1. The median age of the patients in the study was 55 years.
2. The median time from surgery for the patients was 25 months.
3. The range of time from surgery for the patients was between 25 to 288 months in one group and 25 to 294 months in another.
4. There were 18 cases of in situ carcinoma in one group and 24 in another.
5. The oestrogen receptor (ER) was positive in 75 patients in one group and 68 in another.
6. The oestrogen receptor (ER) was negative in 70 patients in one group and 57 in another.
7. The oestrogen receptor (ER) status was unknown in 72 patients in one group and 91 in another.
